name: sfchronicle
text:
BREAKING: Two people died and three others were injured in a shooting near San Jose State University on Tuesday night, police said.

Story by @ByLHernandez: https://t.co/zmaIdXF28o

name: sfchronicle
text:
@ByLHernandez San Jose police released few details on Tuesday night, but said officers responded to a report of one person being shot at about 10 p.m. in the 600 block of S. 8th Street in Downtown San Jose.

https://t.co/VXjmo0zsbb

name: sfchronicle
text:
@ByLHernandez Officers found five people with at least one gun-shot wound each, San Jose police spokesman Sgt. Christian Camarillo said in a statement.

https://t.co/VXjmo0zsbb

name: sfchronicle
text:
@ByLHernandez Two people, whose names were not immediately released on Tuesday night, died at the scene. Three other victims were taken to local hospitals for treatment, Camarillo said. Their conditions were unknown on Tuesday night.

https://t.co/VXjmo0zsbb
